Version: 0.1.8
Date: 2026-04-12

Changes:
- Interactive permission tri-state:
  interactive approval now supports three choices:
  1) yes
  2) no
  3) yes and remember for the same request in current session.
  This reduces repeated approval prompts during tool retries.
- Runtime loop guardrails:
  added automatic no-progress detection for consecutive all-error
  tool batches and mutation-oscillation detection for successful
  inverse file operations (for example create/delete on same path).
  Runtime now injects corrective replanning hints before loops worsen.
- File path shape hardening:
  file mutation tools now reject malformed path-like tokens
  (placeholder-only tokens, template residues, control/ANSI sequences,
  and unsupported ~/ shorthand) before attempting IO.
- Tool path validation unification:
  `create_file` and `edit_file` now reuse shared fs validation logic,
  aligning behavior with other file tools.
- Test coverage:
  added unit tests for permission tri-state + remember behavior,
  runtime no-progress/oscillation guardrails,
  and malformed path rejection for file tools.

